Amazon.com Inc Issues Q4 2012 Guidance
Thursday, 25 Oct 2012 04:00pm EDT
Amazon.com Inc announced that for the fourth quarter of 2012, it expects net sales to be between $20.25 billion and $22.75 billion and operating income (loss) to be between $(490) million and $310 million. This guidance includes approximately $290 million for stock-based compensation and amortization of intangible assets, and it assumes, among other things, that no additional business acquisitions, investments or legal settlements are concluded and that there are no further revisions to stock-based compensation estimates.Â 
